rComments: - lectures are boring (i stopped going after the midterms but still got a b+) - just read the tb - confusing marking scheme - keep checking masteringbiology bc theres always quizzes and she never makes announcemnts about them - there's one group presentation in november - dont expect a study guide from her
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dr. Williams is a professor who wants the best for students by encouraging them to grasp the knowledge behind biological sciences. She makes her lectures interesting by performing small skits and group activities in and out of class so that course content can be understood better. She is a tough grader, but it is most fair for a biology course.
Great professor, very clear and concise, tests on material actually learned in the lectures.

It was just a Research 101 course with animal background info. Her lectures don't even help. Just focus on the slides and for any graph she posts, go to the original paper for you to understand it. She wouldn't explain it better and she wouldnt put any notes on it for conference presentation's sake (she feels like presenting instead of teaching).

I really don't understand how someone so disorganized and unable to teach can land a job as a prof. The tutorials have nothing to with the course content, and the TA doesn't teach or do jack to help. This course is supposed to be equivalent to a high school bio course, but it honestly feels like the course was set up for students to fail.
This prof is the WORST prof at Uoft. Please don't take her class unless you want to fail. Her answers to all your questions will always be "email Pearson". She shouldn't even be teaching.

This prof is terrible, useless lecture notes, does not know how to teach, and makes her quizzes and tests irrelevant. Hard marker for no reason, the class average for the midterm was a 56% for an A level course, no bell curve. Worst prof i've ever had.
The worst professor I've ever had. When she asks a question and no one understands what she was saying, she just skips the slide and moves on to the next topic. Unclear explanations.

By far the worst professor that I have had at U of T in three years! Avoid her classes like the plague - she can't teach to save her life, her lectures are not in logical order and you should read the textbook because it actually explains the material clearly. Is also extremely unreasonable and unhelpful and doesn't clearly explain expectations.
Worst professor uoft has to offer.

Her lecture resembles some ancient labyrinth of sort, filled with magic power and mystery that deter the men and women who dare to explore. Every time I go to her class, I cant help but question my life in despair, and ask myself, constantly, why I took this course.

little care seems to be put into organizing lectures and too much emphasis is put on research applications, while the foundational knowledge necessary for those applications is glossed over. Will not answer a question- there's a difference between leading someone to an answer and simply refusing to help them.

Lectures are very bizarre, she doesn't cover book content instead focuses on case studies of HIV and how to conduct research on it. Tutorials are all over the place, concept not well explained and quize's are TOUGH! She is also very rude! She posts a video to be tested on 1 hour before class? unprofessional!
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Dr. Williams is a wonderful prof! She truly cares about students and their education. Unlike most other profs I have had she takes the time to not simply provide students with answers, rather she helps them to get there on their own. For some students this level of independent thinking is 'hard', but I believe it was most useful even in grad school

I took B51 with prof. Everything she teaches, with examples, is highly likely to show up on the exams and questions are often repetitive. Definitely attend her lectures as she gives many hints on what will be on the exam. Her tutorials are also helpful but the group work is not the best when doing quizzes together. Textbook is helpful for more info

Professor Karen Williams is a very nice lady, had a few conversations; great talk. BUT terrible professor. Asking questions, sounding unsure of her lecture material and referring you to the textbook is practically the epitome of her teaching style. She is a verbatim of a textbook but at least you can get information of a textbook and not her
She doesn't seem to teach the course material very effectively

Personally, I thought she was really nice and her lectures were straight forward and simple! She gives sample questions during class which usually ends up being on the midterm/final. She gives us quizzes and assignments in order to boost our mark and honestly if you go to her she will do her best to explain material to you!

Likely a very nice lady, but she shouldn't be teaching. Don't bother asking her questions, she won't answer them. It's always a big mystery studying for her tests because you have no idea what she taught/wants you to know. Advice - watch lectures & do readings, but SUPPLEMENT your notes, type up the lecture notes. Worst prof I've ever had.

honestly just awful. she won't give you any important definitions or information, and she's terrible at explaining concepts. she'll ramble on about random examples for ages. you never know what she wants from you, her quiz questions are so weird.

Terrible professor in terms of teaching!! I would not recommend taking her class unless you absolutely have to. not only she doesn't explain concepts clearly, but if you ask her question she will ask you the question back -- useless!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: This prof isn't that good of a teacher, when it comes to teaching us the concepts of BIOB51. Main issue with her is that she reads off the slides as if she doesn't know what she's talking about. Her tutorials are awful!

Reads off the slides. Not clear in explaining the slides. 3 hours of lengthy, useless time. Review Lecture right before the exam consisted off topics we should know on the exam. This should have been done at least 1 week prior or she should have explained concepts. Advice is to read slides carefully and study the book for supplementary material.

Extremely easy tests which are basically comprised of questions which she gives to you during lectures. Study those and you'll basically guaranteed to get an 80. If you have a group, you can ask if she can come to your study group to answer any questions. Very helpful prof and will be taking bio with her in the summer.

This class is basically a review of gr.12 bio. You don't really need the text book. She's a decent marker and tests are fair but teaching wise she's terrible. Like others mentioned she answers your questions with questions of her own which is basically useless, lecture slides missing a lot of details and have useless lab-like structure. Watch out.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She was a horrible prof teaching wise,  but very easy. Make use of textbook and other online resources and you will be good.

She is not a very helpful prof since she tries to answer questions with her own questions. It is thought provoking, but sometimes more confusing. Her midterm was easy because of the textbook and repeated questions from the quizzes. Her lectures are organized like a lab report and do not really teach content.

Honestly, I did no readings and I got an 84 on the test. Her lecture notes are extremely disorganized and you will have no idea exactly what to know  for the test. Just pray you remember your grade 12 glycolysis.

She is very unclear even teaching the most simple concepts. The way she speaks is difficult to understand. I feel like she does not have a deep understanding of the material because of the way she explains it! I'm sure she knows what she is talking about, but she isn't the person for the job.
Its just not worth watching the lectures, she is very difficult to follow in a lecture. You're better off just reading the text but you can't because she gives so many hints in lecture. Awful.
Very odd teaching method. Not in a good way either. The material is dry. The way she speaks make it hard to understand.

Probably the worst I've had in my four years. She's knowledgeable about the subject, but has no interest in helping you. The textbook is useless and unrelated to the course. For a neuroscience course, there was an extreme lack of content related to neuroscience and her exams have absolutely ridiculous questions on them... AVOID

Worst Prof ever. Not helpful in learning the material at all. I can get over the way she talks but not that her teaching ability is non existent. If she ever does complete a full example in class she misleads you in some way by giving the wrong answer or confusing you with incorrect formula/ method. not enough room to mention all the BS she does.
Awful. She cant talk properly and is very unclear while explaining. Worst prof I've ever had. Also told us how to study for midterm AFTER the midterm.

Teaching needs improvement, but such is compensated for by her easy midterm. From what I recall, questions asked do not require extensive knowledge to do well; just have some idea of what is happening in class and you should be fine. For anyone who might be interested in actually learning, however, it would be best to read from the textbook.
One of the worst profs I've had so far. Boring and very unclear. Delivery of information is just awful and sometimes unnecessary. Read the textbook just so you have a clue of what to know.

This professor is the worst professor I have ever had. She has no structure to her lectures and her lectures are only vaguely related to the readings she assigns. She is very confusing to understand. Her slides are also very unhelpful and dont follow a continuity found in other regularly taught courses.
Horrible professor, can't teach, never stays on topic, unclear and wastes class time. Bad slides, all exam content is lecture-based but on her personal stories. Worst science professor I've ever had.
